aprove.Framework.IntTRS.Nonterm.GeoNonTerm.ReversePolishNotationTree

Class RPNFunctionSymbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • aprove.Framework.IntTRS.Nonterm.GeoNonTerm.ReversePolishNotationTree.RPNNode
      • aprove.Framework.IntTRS.Nonterm.GeoNonTerm.ReversePolishNotationTree.RPNFunctionSymbol

  • public class RPNFunctionSymbol
extends RPNNode
    The RPNFunctionSymbol represents a TRSCompoundTerm within the RPNTree (reverse polish notation tree).
    Since it contains arithmetic operators it contains an enum with the supported arithmetical operators and contains child RPNNode's.
    The ArithmeticSymbol are all binary operators and therefore the RPNFunctionSymbol has two child nodes.
    Author:
    Timo Bergerbusch
    See Also:
    RPNNode, ArithmeticSymbol, UnsupportetArithmeticSymbolException
